The paper deals with the analysis of network structure and community detection in social networks, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also proposes a new approach that incorporates metadata to improve community detection, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Mining (cs.DM).
